      <aside class="tldr-box bg-gray-100 border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] p-6 my-8 rounded" role="complementary" aria-label="Page summary">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">TL;DR</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          Horse breeding software with advanced genetics: predict foal colors across 13+ genes (Bay, Palomino, Buckskin, Tobiano, Overo, and more), screen for 16+ health conditions (OLWS, HYPP, HERDA, GBED), track mare reproductive cycles with follicle exams and ovulation confirmation, manage 11-month pregnancies with milestone checklists, coordinate stallion services with revenue tracking, and professionally manage high-value horse buyers with built-in CRM.
        </p>
      </aside>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Horse breeding operates on different timescales than small animals. Eleven-month gestation. Seasonal cycling. Higher stakes per breeding. Complex ownership arrangements. Sophisticated genetics. High-value sales requiring professional buyer management.
      </p>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        Generic breeding software doesn't account for any of this. BreederHQ was built specifically for how equine breeding actually works.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 2: The Stakes -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">When your breeding program outgrows basic tools</h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Equine breeding programs hit complexity at different points than small animal operations:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-lg text-gray-700">
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Managing seasonal cycling across multiple mares with individual patterns</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Coordinating with stallion owners, breeding facilities, and semen shipments</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Tracking AI timing, follicle development, and ovulation confirmation</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Understanding color genetics and avoiding dangerous combinations like OLWS</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Managing 11-month pregnancies with critical milestone checkpoints</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>High-value transactions requiring professional documentation and buyer management</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Foaling schedules that can't be missed</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-6 font-semibold">
        The stakes are higher. The timelines are longer. The genetics are complex. The margin for error is smaller.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 3: Genetics Lab -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Genetics Lab: Know What You'll Get Before You Breed</h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
        Stop guessing what colors your foals will be. Stop worrying about dangerous genetic combinations. BreederHQ's Genetics Lab gives you data-driven breeding decisions.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Coat Color Predictions</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            See what colors your foals could be before breeding. BreederHQ predicts outcomes for 13+ horse color genes:
          </p>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-gray-700">
            <ul class="space-y-2">
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="mr-3">•</span>
                <span>Bay, Black, Chestnut (Extension/Agouti)</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="mr-3">•</span>
                <span>Palomino, Buckskin, Cremello (Cream)</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="mr-3">•</span>
                <span>Dun, Red Dun, Grullo</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="mr-3">•</span>
                <span>Gray (progressive graying)</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
            <ul class="space-y-2">
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="mr-3">•</span>
                <span>Roan (true roan pattern)</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="mr-3">•</span>
                <span>Tobiano, Overo, Sabino (Paint patterns)</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="mr-3">•</span>
                <span>Champagne, Pearl</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="mr-3">•</span>
                <span>Leopard Complex (Appaloosa)</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-red-800">Health Risk Assessment</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Automatically flags dangerous genetic combinations. BreederHQ screens for 16+ inherited conditions:
          </p>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-gray-700">
            <ul class="space-y-2">
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="mr-3 text-red-600">⚠</span>
                <span><strong>OLWS/LWO</strong> — Lethal White Overo Syndrome</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="mr-3 text-red-600">⚠</span>
                <span><strong>HYPP</strong> — Hyperkalemic Periodic Paralysis</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="mr-3 text-red-600">⚠</span>
                <span><strong>HERDA</strong> — Hereditary Equine Regional Dermal Asthenia</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="mr-3 text-red-600">⚠</span>
                <span><strong>GBED</strong> — Glycogen Branching Enzyme Deficiency</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
            <ul class="space-y-2">
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="mr-3 text-red-600">⚠</span>
                <span><strong>PSSM1</strong> — Polysaccharide Storage Myopathy</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="mr-3 text-red-600">⚠</span>
                <span><strong>MH</strong> — Malignant Hyperthermia</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="mr-3 text-red-600">⚠</span>
                <span><strong>WFFS</strong> — Warmblood Fragile Foal Syndrome</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="mr-3 text-red-600">⚠</span>
                <span>Plus SCID, CA, LFS, JEB, and more</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mt-4 italic">
            The system warns you before you make a carrier-to-carrier breeding that could produce affected foals.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Inbreeding Coefficient (COI)</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              Analyzes up to 10 generations of pedigree to calculate inbreeding risk. Color-coded risk levels (Low, Moderate, High, Critical) help you make informed decisions about genetic diversity.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Punnett Square Visualization</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              See visual inheritance grids showing exactly how genes combine for each trait. Understand the probabilities, not just the possibilities.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Offspring Simulator</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              Run Monte Carlo simulations to see what 20 random foals might look like from any pairing. Understand the range of possible outcomes before you commit.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Best Match Finder</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              Automatically ranks all your stallions (or mares) to find the optimal breeding match based on genetics, health risks, and COI. Stop guessing which pairing is best.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 4: Mare Reproductive Management -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Mare Reproductive Management</h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
        Seasonal cycling. Individual mare patterns. Optimal breeding windows. BreederHQ tracks it all so you don't miss the right moment.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Heat Cycle Tracking</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Record cycle dates and predict upcoming heats based on your mare's individual patterns. See historical cycles to understand her specific rhythm—not just textbook averages.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Follicle Exam Recording</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
